# StudySmart Environment Variables Example

## BACKEND ENVIRONMENT (.env in /backend)

# Flask settings
FLASK_ENV=development
FLASK_DEBUG=True
SECRET_KEY=your_secret_key_here_change_in_production

# Server settings
HOST=0.0.0.0
PORT=5000

# CORS settings (comma-separated list of allowed origins)
CORS_ORIGINS=http://localhost:3000,https://studysmartapp.netlify.app

# Model paths
HAARCASCADE_FACE_PATH=models/haarcascade_frontalface_default.xml
HAARCASCADE_EYE_PATH=models/haarcascade_righteye_2splits.xml
SHAPE_PREDICTOR_PATH=models/shape_predictor_68_face_landmarks.dat

# Feature flags
ENABLE_FACE_DETECTION=True
ENABLE_BLINK_DETECTION=True
ENABLE_HAND_TRACKING=True

# Blink detection threshold (lower = more sensitive)
BLINK_THRESHOLD=0.2

# Logging
LOG_LEVEL=INFO
LOG_FILE=logs/app.log

---

## FRONTEND ENVIRONMENT (.env.local in /new-app)

# Backend API URL
REACT_APP_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:5000

# Environment
REACT_APP_ENV=development

# Feature flags
REACT_APP_ENABLE_ANALYTICS=false
REACT_APP_ENABLE_DEBUG_MODE=false

# Optional: API timeout in milliseconds
REACT_APP_API_TIMEOUT=30000

---

## DOCKER ENVIRONMENT (if using Docker Compose)

# backend service
FLASK_ENV=development
CORS_ORIGINS=http://localhost:3000

# frontend service
REACT_APP_API_BASE_URL=http://backend:5000

---

## PRODUCTION SETTINGS

When using in production:

### Backend
- Change FLASK_ENV to "production"
- Set FLASK_DEBUG to "False"
- Update SECRET_KEY to a strong random value
- Update CORS_ORIGINS to your actual domain
- Set LOG_LEVEL to "WARNING"
- Use a production WSGI server (gunicorn, uWSGI)
- Enable HTTPS

### Frontend
- Change REACT_APP_ENV to "production"
- Update REACT_APP_API_BASE_URL to your production backend URL
- Update REACT_APP_ENABLE_ANALYTICS to "true" if using analytics

---

For full setup instructions, see SETUP_INSTRUCTIONS.md
